The paper proposes an innovative credit risk prediction framework that uses multiple classifiers and fuzzy Choquet integrals to handle uncertainty in P2P lending. This involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG) and computational finance (cs.CE, cs.CR) to improve creditworthiness evaluations. The paper also uses a real-world dataset from a P2P lending marketplace, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
